      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "Mononuclear cells were isolated from BM as previously described, after which the cells were resuspended in low glucose Dulbecco's modified Eagle's medium (DMEM/low glucose; Gibco BRL, Rockville, MD) that was supplemented with 10% fetal bovine serum (FBS; Gibco BRL), 4 mM L-glutamine, 100 U/mL penicillin, 100 mg/mL streptomycin, and 100 mg/mL gentamicin (all reagents were obtained from Gibco BRL); the cells were seeded at a density of 0:2 × 10 6 cells/cm 2 in T-25 culture flasks (Corning, Inc./Costar; New York, NY)."
